news.title: China Evergrande Group suspends share trading again
news.para: Among those embroiled in the crisis is Evergrande, one of the country's largest developers, which has been involved in restructuring negotiations after racking up $300 billion in liabilities.

news.title: Singapore REIT Mapletree Commercial Trust adds cash-only option to $3 billion merger
news.para: Mapletree Commercial Trust (MCT) had announced plans in December to buy Mapletree North Asia Commercial Trust (MNACT), seeking to create the seventh largest real estate investment trust (REIT) in Asia with an expected market value of about S$10.5 billion.

news.title: Streetlights to be installed soon on Mysuru ORR
news.para: All three agencies — service provider Mysuru City Corporation, developer Mysuru Urban Development Authority, and the NHAI, which took over the control five years back, were at loggerheads over installing streetlights, causing great inconvenience to commuters.

news.title: Asian Granito files draft paper for upto Rs. 500 crore rights issue
news.para: The commercial operations in all the three wholly-owned subsidiaries are expected to commence in the beginning of financial year 2023-24. It has estimated that total working capital requirement for all the three companies in the first year of commercial operations in 2023-24 will be around Rs 80 crore.

news.title: HC stops Maharashtra govt from giving sand mining contract on Savitri river in Raigad
news.para: Hearing three petitions, the HC on March 8, 2022 stayed the State’s auction notice for mechanised sand mining/excavation of various tracts of land across the 11 km stretch from Vicharwadi to Dasgaon.

news.title: Analytix Business Solutions leases 70,000 sq ft office space in Ahmedabad
news.para: Realistic Realtors facilitated the office space transaction. The tri-party agreement has been facilitated between Sun Builders Group, The Address and Analytix Business Solutions.

news.title: Rispana hillocks illegally flattened for construction, causing landslides: Activists
news.para: Residents allege that in recent times the area has also become prone to landslides due to the ongoing construction activities.

news.title: Maharashtra realtors plan to stop construction as raw material price surge continues
news.para: Realty developers have also requested the Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority to extend the deadline for completion of ongoing projects by at least 6 months so that they get time to pause construction activity until prices rationalise.

news.title: Nagpur: Rising steel prices due to war may make homes costlier, say builders
news.para: The builders claim that it may ultimately lead to an increase of 20% to 30% in the selling price of real estate in new projects.

news.title: Maharashtra government sanctions Rs 250 crore for Mumbai metro-3 line
news.para: The underground Metro Line 3 project was to be commissioned in 2019 in time for the then state elections but construction of tunnels and stations has been delayed.

news.title: Government will sanction more houses for Dharwad: Karnataka housing minister
news.para: During the bhoomi puja for the construction work of 235 houses in Kundagol town on Saturday, Somanna said 4,075 houses have already been sanctioned to urban areas of the district.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: VMRDA races against time to finish one-cent layouts
news.para: The VMRDA is developing 56 layouts on about 4,000 acres in different parts of Visakhapatnam district for distribution of house sites to about 1.8 lakh homeless poor.

news.title: Draw of lots for over 110 flats in Greater Noida
news.para: Officials from the authority said that the first draw will be among applicants who have opted for lump sum payment. After that, there will be a draw among the applicants opting for payment in instalments.

news.title: Over 125 commercial projects under construction in Nashik
news.para: Earlier, commercial projects were limited only to posh commercial market areas like College Road, Mahatma Nagar, M G Road and Main Road areas of the city. But now the projects are coming up at Mhasrul, Adgaon, Pathardi, Untawadi, Govind Nagar and Indira Nagar.

news.title: No MOFA rights to flat purchasers on project on MMRDA land: Bombay HC
news.para: The Court held that the MMRDA Act expressly excludes the applicability of MOFA entirely from lands belonging to or vested in MMRDA.
